
Bien sûr, voici un message que tu pourrais envoyer :

---

**Objet : Suivi sur l’ouverture de flux**  

Bonjour [Nom],  

J’espère que tu vas bien. Comme toi, je subis cette situation compliquée liée au flux réseau fermé qui nous bloque et nous pénalise. Je voulais savoir si tu avais eu des nouvelles à ce sujet ou si tu pouvais en obtenir auprès du service compétent.  

J’ai déjà effectué une relance, mais sans retour pour le moment. Il est possible qu’il y ait eu une erreur dans ma demande initiale, mais sans information, difficile de corriger le tir.  

Si tu as le moindre élément ou si tu peux nous aider à y voir plus clair, ce serait vraiment précieux.  

Merci d’avance pour ton aide et ton soutien.  

À bientôt,  
[Ta signature]  

---

Ce message reste courtois tout en exprimant clairement l’urgence du problème. Tu peux bien sûr le modifier selon ton ton habituel. J’espère que cela pourra faire avancer les choses !





Here is your message translated into English:  

---

**Subject: Appreciation and regret regarding the invitation to the strategic committee**  

Dear [Contact Name],  

I sincerely thank you for your kind invitation to participate, as a client and privileged member, in the strategic committee bringing together experts on your ChangeMan product in the United States. It is a valuable opportunity that reflects our relationship and your consideration.  

Unfortunately, as I do not speak English and my company does not allow me to attend, I will not be able to be present. However, please know that I would have been delighted to take part in these enriching discussions.  

Once again, I appreciate your invitation and wish you great success for this event. I look forward to exchanging with you on another occasion.  

Best regards,  
[Your Name]  

---

This translation keeps your message professional and polite while maintaining the intended tone. Let me know if you’d like any refinements! 😊






Of course! Here’s your message translated into English:

---

**Hello,**  

I apologize for my late response; I was on leave.  

After being approached by Société Générale, Euroclear is now showing interest in our experience with ChangeMan. Beyond its intrinsic qualities, this meeting will be an opportunity to present XML services and REST APIs, highlighting our tools and trajectory. Indeed, our developments are based on Java and Python.  

I had originally planned this presentation in French, but we can absolutely adapt since my colleague is fluent in English. As for my English… let's just say it's quite rough, and your ears might suffer! 😆 I will send you the invitation.  

Furthermore, Claudio Monzini has written to me about joining a CAB, which is expected to be planned as an autonomous initiative.  

---

This keeps the meaning and tone intact, including your humor! Let me know if you'd like any refinements. 😊

















